<font color="#FF0000">LET'S STOP AND TAKE A BREATH</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug 14 12:24:02 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well, I have not posted here in a long while because I was busy, and reading only one thread (we only have time for so much).  Now that I have read some of the more recent posts, I feel a need to comment.<br><br>
A long time ago, I got on people for their use of language on this site.  It looks like that is appropriate again now.  Please realize that this site is open to the whole world, and we are acting as representatives of our particular point of view to anyone who may wish to read these postings.  Some of the recent ones, I would be hesitant to have my teenage boys read.<br><br>
To Doc Spatz:  You may think you won a great victory recently, but you forefooted it with the venom of your post.  You asked why no one had taken certain individuals to task for their references to other peoples in a racist way.  I haven't been reading this post, and so couldn't until now.<br><br>
To Cook:  I have admired much of your writings, but I feel that you have stepped over some bounds with some of your language and references to people.  Please realize that some of us DO take offence at your references to Asians as *****.  I happen to be married to an Asian woman, so BACK OFF on the use of that kind of language.<br><br>
To all of you who posted recently, I can only say that you remind me of a county fair greased pig contest.  Many kids chase the greased pig, rarely is it caught, but everyone gets dirty in the process.  <br><br>
I hope that you can work as hard at finding common ground as you have in your name-calling.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


